---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';

const routes = SITE.commercial.routes;
const subject = encodeURIComponent('Compute Current sample brief request');
const body = encodeURIComponent('Please send the current Compute Current Pro sample brief and founding subscriber details.');
const sampleHref = `mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}?subject=${subject}&body=${body}`;
---
<Layout
  title={`Sample Brief | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="A sample Compute Current premium decision memo on AI data centers, power access, capacity, capital exposure, and infrastructure bottlenecks."
  canonicalPath={routes.sample}
>
  <main class="policy-shell commercial-page commercial-page-sample">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Latest analysis</a>
    <article class="policy-page commercial-article">
      <header class="commercial-hero">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Sample Decision Memo</p>
          <h1>AI Data Centers Are Turning Power Access Into the New Capacity Moat</h1>
          <p class="policy-lede">
            This is an illustrative sample of the paid Compute Current memo format. It shows the commercial read,
            watch items, and confidence notes a subscriber would receive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="commercial-hero-note" aria-label="Sample memo use">
          <span>Memo format</span>
          <strong>Commercial read first</strong>
          <p>Every premium brief separates what changed from who benefits, who is exposed, and what to watch next.</p>
        </aside>
      </header>

      <nav class="commercial-actions" aria-label="Sample brief actions">
        <a href={sampleHref}>Request the Current Sample</a>
        <a href={routes.subscribe}>Get the Weekly Brief</a>
        <a href={routes.pricing}>See Pricing</a>
      </nav>

      <section class="commercial-section commercial-sample-lead">
        <h2>What changed</h2>
        <div class="commercial-sample-block">
          <h3>Power access is becoming the gating constraint for AI capacity.</h3>
          <p>
            The sample read assumes a market where land, fiber, and capital are available, but usable power,
            interconnection timing, and cooling design decide which AI data center projects can move first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="commercial-section commercial-memo-grid">
        <div class="commercial-note">
          <h2>Why it matters for AI infrastructure</h2>
          <p>
            AI capacity decisions now depend on grid timing, utility coordination, behind-the-meter options,
            rack density, cooling readiness, and the ability to sequence power delivery with tenant commitments.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="commercial-note">
          <h2>Confidence notes</h2>
          <p>
            Confidence is medium in this illustrative sample because the thesis is directional and depends on
            project-level evidence. A live Pro memo would attach source URLs, confidence labels, and item-specific caveats.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="commercial-section commercial-proof-grid">
        <div>
          <h2>Who benefits</h2>
          <ul class="commercial-signal-list">
            <li>Operators with defined power positions and credible energization timelines.</li>
            <li>Developers that can combine grid access, generation strategy, and tenant-ready campus phasing.</li>
            <li>Equipment and cooling vendors tied to high-density deployments with near-term power availability.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Who is exposed</h2>
          <ul class="commercial-signal-list">
            <li>Projects marketed as AI-ready before utility milestones are firm.</li>
            <li>Capital plans that assume GPU demand can overcome grid or permitting delay.</li>
            <li>Teams tracking MW headlines without checking deliverability, cooling design, and interconnection queue risk.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="commercial-section">
        <h2>Watch next</h2>
        <ul class="commercial-signal-list commercial-check-grid">
          <li>Interconnection dates that move from planning language to executable utility milestones.</li>
          <li>Campus expansions paired with generation, storage, nuclear, gas, or renewable supply strategy.</li>
          <li>Tenant commitments that specify phased capacity delivery rather than headline MW alone.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
